#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:5
msgid "The Linux NTFS filesystem driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:16
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:18
msgid ""
"NTFS is a Linux kernel filesystem driver that provides full read and write "
"support for NTFS volumes. It is designed for high performance, modern kernel "
"infrastructure (iomap, folio), and stable long-term maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:24
msgid "Utilities support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:26
msgid ""
"The NTFS utilities project, called ntfsprogs-plus, provides mkfs.ntfs, fsck."
"ntfs, and other related tools (e.g., ntfsinfo, ntfsclone, etc.) for "
"creating, checking, and managing NTFS volumes. These utilities can be used "
"for filesystem testing with xfstests as well as for recovering corrupted "
"NTFS devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:32
msgid "The project is available at:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:34
msgid "https://github.com/ntfsprogs-plus/ntfsprogs-plus"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:38
msgid "Supported mount options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:40
msgid "The NTFS driver supports the following mount options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:43
msgid "iocharset=name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:43
msgid ""
"Character set to use for converting between the encoding is used for user "
"visible filename and 16 bit Unicode characters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:47
msgid "nls=name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:47
msgid ""
"Deprecated option.  Still supported but please use iocharset=name in the "
"future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:50
msgid "uid="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:51
msgid "gid="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:52
msgid "umask="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:52
msgid ""
"Provide default owner, group, and access mode mask. These options work as "
"documented in mount(8).  By default, the files/directories are owned by root "
"and he/she has read and write permissions, as well as browse permission for "
"directories.  No one else has any access permissions.  I.e. the mode on all "
"files is by default rw------- and for directories rwx------, a consequence "
"of the default fmask=0177 and dmask=0077. Using a umask of zero will grant "
"all permissions to everyone, i.e. all files and directories will have mode "
"rwxrwxrwx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:65
msgid "fmask="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:66
msgid "dmask="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:66
msgid ""
"Instead of specifying umask which applies both to files and directories, "
"fmask applies only to files and dmask only to directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:70
msgid "showmeta=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:71
msgid "show_sys_files=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:71
msgid ""
"If show_sys_files is specified, show the system files in directory "
"listings.  Otherwise the default behaviour is to hide the system files. Note "
"that even when show_sys_files is specified, \"$MFT\" will not be visible due "
"to bugs/mis-features in glibc. Further, note that irrespective of "
"show_sys_files, all files are accessible by name, i.e. you can always do "
"\"ls -l \\$UpCase\" for example to specifically show the system file "
"containing the Unicode upcase table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:82
msgid "case_sensitive=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:82
msgid ""
"If case_sensitive is specified, treat all filenames as case sensitive and "
"create file names in the POSIX namespace (default behavior). Note, the Linux "
"NTFS driver will never create short filenames and will remove them on rename/"
"delete of the corresponding long file name. Note that files remain "
"accessible via their short file name, if it exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:91
msgid "nocase=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:91
msgid "If nocase is specified, treat filenames case-insensitively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:94
msgid "disable_sparse=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:94
msgid ""
"If disable_sparse is specified, creation of sparse regions, i.e. holes, "
"inside files is disabled for the volume (for the duration of this mount "
"only). By default, creation of sparse regions is enabled, which is "
"consistent with the behaviour of traditional Unix filesystems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:101
msgid "errors=opt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:101
msgid ""
"Specify NTFS behavior on critical errors: panic, remount the partition in "
"read-only mode or continue without doing anything (default behavior)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:105
msgid "mft_zone_multiplier="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:105
msgid ""
"Set the MFT zone multiplier for the volume (this setting is not persistent "
"across mounts and can be changed from mount to mount but cannot be changed "
"on remount).  Values of 1 to 4 are allowed, 1 being the default.  The MFT "
"zone multiplier determines how much space is reserved for the MFT on the "
"volume.  If all other space is used up, then the MFT zone will be shrunk "
"dynamically, so this has no impact on the amount of free space.  However, it "
"can have an impact on performance by affecting fragmentation of the MFT. In "
"general use the default.  If you have a lot of small files then use a higher "
"value.  The values have the following meaning:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:121
msgid "Value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:121
msgid "MFT zone size (% of volume size)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:123
msgid "1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:123
msgid "12.5%"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:124
msgid "2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:124
msgid "25%"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:125
msgid "3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:125
msgid "37.5%"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:126
msgid "4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:126
msgid "50%"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:129
msgid "Note this option is irrelevant for read-only mount."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:131
msgid "preallocated_size="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:131
msgid ""
"Set preallocated size to optimize runlist merge overhead with small chunck "
"size.(64KB size by default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:135
msgid "acl=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:135
msgid ""
"Enable POSIX ACL support. When specified, POSIX ACLs stored in extended "
"attributes are enforced. Default is off. Requires kernel config "
"NTFS_FS_POSIX_ACL enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:140
msgid "sys_immutable=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:140
msgid ""
"Make NTFS system files (e.g. $MFT, $LogFile, $Bitmap, $UpCase, etc.) "
"immutable to user initiated modifications for extra safety. Default is off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:144
msgid "nohidden=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:144
msgid ""
"Hide files and directories marked with the Windows \"hidden\" attribute. By "
"default hidden items are shown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:148
msgid "hide_dot_files=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:148
msgid ""
"Hide names beginning with a dot (\".\"). By default dot files are shown. "
"When enabled, files and directories created with a leading '.' will be "
"hidden from directory listings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:153
msgid "windows_names=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:153
msgid ""
"Refuse creation/rename of files with characters or reserved device names "
"disallowed on Windows (e.g. CON, NUL, AUX, COM1, LPT1, etc.). Default is off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:156
msgid "discard=<BOOL>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/ntfs.rst:156
msgid ""
"Issue block device discard for clusters freed on file deletion/truncation to "
"inform underlying storage."
msgstr ""
